This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it discusses the Liquid State Machine (LSM) architecture, which is a type of recurrent neural network. Additionally, the paper proposes a new metric for evaluating LSM performance, which is related to the network's memory capacity. 

The paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the use of LSMs for solving problems like speech recognition and time series prediction. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses a brain-inspired architecture and its performance on various tasks. 

The Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is another possibility as the paper proposes a new metric for evaluating the performance of a dynamical system. 

Finally, the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category could also be a possibility as the paper discusses the use of LSMs for speech recognition, which is a natural language processing task.
